---
/**
 * Malta Digital Nomad Visa - Long-form CRO-optimized page
 * Static page (overrides dynamic route for this specific country)
 */

import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", text: "Overview", level: 2 },
  { id: "quick-decision", text: "Quick Decision Guide", level: 2 },
  { id: "requirements", text: "Visa Requirements", level: 2 },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", text: "Insurance Requirements", level: 2 },
  { id: "recommended-providers", text: "Recommended Providers", level: 2 },
  { id: "costs", text: "Costs Breakdown", level: 2 },
  { id: "application", text: "Application Process", level: 2 },
  { id: "scenarios", text: "Real-World Scenarios", level: 2 },
  { id: "mistakes", text: "Common Mistakes", level: 2 },
  { id: "healthcare", text: "Healthcare in Malta", level: 2 },
  { id: "faq", text: "FAQ", level: 2 },
  { id: "verdict", text: "Final Verdict", level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: "Malta Health Insurance Guide", href: "/countries/malta/insurance" },
  { title: "Insurance for Digital Nomads", href: "/insurance-for/digital-nomads" },
  { title: "Best Expat Health Insurance", href: "/best/expat-health-insurance" },
];

const requirementsColumns = [
  { key: "requirement", header: "Requirement" },
  { key: "details", header: "Details" },
  { key: "evidence", header: "Evidence Needed" },
];

const requirementsRows = [
  { requirement: "Annual Income", details: "€2,700/month (€32,400/year)", evidence: "Employment contract, bank statements" },
  { requirement: "Remote Work", details: "Work for employer outside Malta", evidence: "Employment letter" },
  { requirement: "Health Insurance", details: "Mandatory full coverage", evidence: "Insurance certificate" },
  { requirement: "Valid Passport", details: "6+ months beyond intended stay", evidence: "Passport copy" },
  { requirement: "Accommodation", details: "Proof of Malta address", evidence: "Rental contract" },
];

const insuranceColumns = [
  { key: "feature", header: "Coverage Feature" },
  { key: "minimum", header: "Malta Requirement" },
  { key: "why", header: "Why It Matters" },
];

const insuranceRows = [
  { feature: "Medical Coverage", minimum: "€30,000+ (Schengen)", why: "EU minimum standard" },
  { feature: "Hospitalization", minimum: "Full coverage", why: "Required for permit" },
  { feature: "Repatriation", minimum: "Required", why: "Schengen requirement" },
  { feature: "Coverage Duration", minimum: "Full permit period", why: "1 year minimum" },
  { feature: "Malta Territory", minimum: "Must be covered", why: "Specifically listed" },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: "provider", header: "Provider" },
  { key: "coverage", header: "Coverage" },
  { key: "price", header: "Monthly Cost" },
  { key: "strengths", header: "Best For" },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: "SafetyWing", coverage: "€250,000", price: "€40-75", strengths: "Budget nomads" },
  { provider: "Cigna Global", coverage: "€1,000,000+", price: "€180-350", strengths: "Comprehensive" },
  { provider: "Allianz Care", coverage: "€500,000+", price: "€150-300", strengths: "EU network" },
  { provider: "BUPA Global", coverage: "€2,000,000+", price: "€280-450", strengths: "Premium" },
  { provider: "Laferla (Local)", coverage: "Varies", price: "€60-150", strengths: "Malta-specific" },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: "item", header: "Cost Item" },
  { key: "amount", header: "Amount (EUR)" },
  { key: "notes", header: "Notes" },
];

const costRows = [
  { item: "Nomad Residence Permit", amount: "€300", notes: "Application fee" },
  { item: "Residence Card", amount: "€27.50", notes: "Physical card" },
  { item: "Health Insurance (Annual)", amount: "€500-3,500", notes: "Varies by provider" },
  { item: "Background Check", amount: "€50-100", notes: "If required" },
  { item: "Document Authentication", amount: "€30-80", notes: "Apostilles if needed" },
];

const timelineColumns = [
  { key: "step", header: "Step" },
  { key: "duration", header: "Timeline" },
  { key: "location", header: "Where" },
];

const timelineRows = [
  { step: "Gather documents", duration: "1-2 weeks", location: "Home country" },
  { step: "Submit application online", duration: "1-2 hours", location: "Residency Malta portal" },
  { step: "Processing", duration: "4-6 weeks", location: "Residency Malta Agency" },
  { step: "Receive approval", duration: "Via email", location: "Digital" },
  { step: "Travel to Malta", duration: "Within 1 month of approval", location: "Malta" },
  { step: "Collect residence card", duration: "After arrival", location: "Identity Malta" },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Malta Digital Nomad Visa 2025: Insurance Requirements & Complete Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Malta's Nomad Residence Permit. €2,700/month income requirement, Mediterranean island living, and application process."
  headline="Malta Digital Nomad Visa: Insurance & Requirements Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about working remotely from Malta—insurance requirements, costs, and island life in the EU."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Qualifying Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated January 2025
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Residency Malta
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      EU/Schengen Member
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta launched its Nomad Residence Permit in June 2021, offering remote workers a path to live on this Mediterranean island nation while working for foreign employers. As an EU and Schengen member, Malta provides full European access with English as an official language.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's unique selling point is the combination of Mediterranean lifestyle, English-speaking environment, and established expat infrastructure. The islands are small but well-connected, with excellent internet and a growing tech/gaming industry.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Malta Nomad Residence Permit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> 1 year, renewable up to 3 years total</li>
        <li>• <strong>Income requirement:</strong> €2,700/month (€32,400/year)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Processing time:</strong> 4-6 weeks typical</li>
        <li>• <strong>Insurance:</strong> Mandatory full coverage</li>
        <li>• <strong>Language:</strong> English is official—no language barrier</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Malta for Digital Nomads?</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>English-speaking:</strong> No language barrier for daily life or bureaucracy</li>
      <li><strong>EU/Schengen:</strong> Full European travel freedom</li>
      <li><strong>Mediterranean weather:</strong> 300+ sunny days per year</li>
      <li><strong>Tech hub:</strong> Strong iGaming and fintech industry</li>
      <li><strong>Safe:</strong> Very low crime, stable environment</li>
      <li><strong>Compact:</strong> Everything within 30 minutes</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Malta is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ You earn €2,700+/month from remote work</li>
          <li>✓ You want English-speaking EU country</li>
          <li>✓ You enjoy Mediterranean island lifestyle</li>
          <li>✓ You work Europe/Africa/Middle East time zones</li>
          <li>✓ You value safety and stability</li>
          <li>✓ You appreciate compact, walkable environments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You want very low cost of living</li>
          <li>• You prefer mountains or large green spaces</li>
          <li>• You dislike crowded, touristy areas</li>
          <li>• You want a large digital nomad community</li>
          <li>• You need space and privacy</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Visa Requirements -->
  <section id="requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's Nomad Residence Permit has clear requirements. The €2,700/month income threshold is moderate, and the process is straightforward for an EU country.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={requirementsColumns} rows={requirementsRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Income Verification</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      You must demonstrate €32,400 annual income (€2,700/month). Accepted evidence includes:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Employment contract:</strong> Showing salary from foreign employer</li>
      <li><strong>Bank statements:</strong> 3-6 months showing income deposits</li>
      <li><strong>Tax returns:</strong> Previous year's income documentation</li>
      <li><strong>For freelancers:</strong> Client contracts and invoices</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Accommodation First:</strong> You need proof of Malta accommodation before applying. Secure a rental contract or property before submitting your application.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Document Checklist</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Valid passport (6+ months validity)</li>
      <li>Passport photos (Schengen specifications)</li>
      <li>Proof of income (€2,700+/month)</li>
      <li>Health insurance certificate</li>
      <li>Employment contract or business documentation</li>
      <li>Proof of accommodation in Malta</li>
      <li>CV/resume</li>
      <li>Clean criminal record (if requested)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Comprehensive Coverage Required</h3>
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        Malta requires health insurance covering all risks across Malta for the entire duration of your stay. This must meet Schengen standards: €30,000+ coverage, hospitalization, and repatriation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Health insurance is mandatory for Malta's Nomad Residence Permit. Your policy must specifically list Malta as covered territory and extend for your full permit duration.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Coverage Requirements</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Malta Healthcare Context</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Public Healthcare</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• <strong>Access:</strong> Limited for non-residents</li>
          <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Good, EU standards</li>
          <li>• <strong>Emergency:</strong> Mater Dei Hospital 24/7</li>
          <li>• <strong>Language:</strong> English widely spoken</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Private Healthcare</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• <strong>Access:</strong> With international insurance</li>
          <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Excellent</li>
          <li>• <strong>Language:</strong> English standard</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cost:</strong> Moderate</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's small size means all healthcare is centralized. Mater Dei Hospital in Birkirkara handles most serious cases. Private clinics are available for routine care.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox variant="highlight">
    <p class="mb-4">Need insurance that meets Malta's requirements?</p>
    <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-white text-primary-700 font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-50 transition-colors" style="color: #1d4ed8 !important;">
      Compare Qualifying Plans →
    </a>
  </CTABox>

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      These providers offer coverage that meets Malta's Nomad Residence Permit requirements:
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Budget Nomads</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">SafetyWing at €40-75/month. Meets requirements at lowest cost.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Local Option</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Laferla Insurance. Malta-based, knows local requirements, good local network.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Comprehensive Global</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cigna Global or Allianz Care. Full EU coverage with worldwide benefits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Premium Coverage</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">BUPA Global. Top-tier coverage with best private facility access.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Costs Breakdown -->
  <section id="costs" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's permit fees are straightforward. Living costs are moderate for the EU—higher than Eastern Europe but lower than Northern Europe.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">First Year Total Cost Estimates</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Budget Setup</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">€900</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Permit + basic insurance</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Standard Setup</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">€2,000</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Permit + mid-tier coverage</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Premium Setup</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">€4,000</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Permit + premium coverage</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cost of Living</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta is moderately expensive. Rent is the main cost. Monthly budgets:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Budget:</strong> €1,500-2,000/month (shared housing, cooking)</li>
      <li><strong>Comfortable:</strong> €2,500-3,500/month (own apartment, dining out)</li>
      <li><strong>Premium:</strong> €4,000+/month (Sliema/St. Julian's, full lifestyle)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's process is largely online through the Residency Malta Agency portal. It's more streamlined than many EU countries.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Secure Accommodation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Find and sign a rental contract in Malta. You need this before applying.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Documentation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Prepare all required documents: income proof, insurance, passport, employment contract, CV.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Online Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply through the Residency Malta Agency portal. Pay the €300 application fee.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Processing</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Processing typically takes 4-6 weeks. You may be contacted for additional information.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Travel to Malta</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Once approved, travel to Malta within 1 month to finalize your residence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Collect Residence Card</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Visit Identity Malta to complete biometrics and collect your physical residence card.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Start apartment hunting before you apply. The Malta rental market can be competitive, especially in popular areas like Sliema, St. Julian's, and Valletta.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Real-World Scenarios -->
  <section id="scenarios" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Here's how different situations typically play out with Malta's Nomad Residence Permit:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">iGaming Professional, €5,000/month</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Works for UK gaming company, wants to be near Malta's gaming hub.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved quickly. Industry connection to Malta seen positively. Living in St. Julian's.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Freelance Developer, €3,500/month</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Multiple international clients, wants English-speaking EU base.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved. Provided client contracts and bank statements as income proof.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Marketing Manager, €2,400/month</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Remote employee for German company, slightly below threshold.</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 font-medium">✗ Denied. €300/month below requirement. Advised to negotiate raise or supplement income.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Crypto/Fintech Founder, €8,000/month</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Runs blockchain company, interested in Malta's crypto-friendly environment.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved. Malta's fintech reputation was a draw. Easy process with clear income.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Writer, €3,000/month</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Author and content creator, wants quiet island life.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved. Income above threshold. Enjoying slower pace in Gozo.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Couple, €4,500/month combined</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Both remote workers, want Mediterranean island base.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Both approved separately. Each met €2,700 threshold individually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox>
    <p class="mb-4">Compare insurance plans for your Malta move—get quotes in minutes.</p>
    <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors" style="color: white !important;">
      Get Insurance Quotes →
    </a>
  </CTABox>

  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">No Accommodation Before Applying</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You need a Malta address with rental contract before you can apply. Don't start the process without housing secured first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Rent Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta rent has increased significantly. Budget €1,200-2,000/month for a decent 1-bedroom in popular areas. Factor this into your budget.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Big Island Feel</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta is tiny (316 km²). You can drive across it in 30-45 minutes. If you need space and nature, this may feel limiting.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Summer Overcrowding</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta gets very crowded in summer with tourists. Beaches, restaurants, and roads are packed July-August. Plan accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insurance Without Malta Listed</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Ensure your policy specifically names Malta as covered territory. Generic "EU coverage" may not be explicitly clear enough.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ignoring Gozo</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta's sister island Gozo is quieter, greener, and cheaper. Consider it as an alternative if Malta proper feels too hectic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Malta -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare in Malta</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta has good healthcare infrastructure concentrated in Mater Dei Hospital. Private clinics handle most routine care. English is standard in all medical settings.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Healthcare Facilities</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Mater Dei Hospital</strong> - Main public hospital, 24/7 emergency</li>
      <li><strong>St. James Hospital</strong> - Private, comprehensive services</li>
      <li><strong>Da Vinci Hospital</strong> - Private, modern facility</li>
      <li><strong>Various clinics</strong> - Private GP and specialist services throughout</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Sample Costs (Without Insurance)</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>GP visit (private):</strong> €30-60</li>
      <li><strong>Specialist:</strong> €50-100</li>
      <li><strong>Emergency room:</strong> €80-200</li>
      <li><strong>Dental cleaning:</strong> €40-70</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-4">
      Healthcare costs are reasonable by European standards. The main limitation is Malta's small size—complex cases may sometimes be referred abroad.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew the Nomad Residence Permit?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. The initial 1-year permit can be renewed for 2 additional years, giving you up to 3 years total. Renewal requires continuing to meet income and insurance requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay Maltese taxes?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Digital nomads are generally taxed only on income remitted to Malta, not worldwide income. However, if you stay 183+ days you may become tax resident. Consult a Maltese tax advisor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in Schengen?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Malta is a Schengen member. Your residence permit allows free travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is there a digital nomad community?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Growing but smaller than Portugal or Bali. Malta has coworking spaces and regular nomad meetups. The iGaming/fintech crowd provides a tech-savvy community.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about driving?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Malta drives on the left (British influence). Roads are narrow and can be chaotic. Many nomads use buses, walking, or ride-sharing. A car is useful but not essential given Malta's size.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Gozo a good option?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, if you prefer quiet. Gozo is greener, cheaper, and less crowded. The trade-off is limited nightlife and a 25-minute ferry to Malta proper. Internet is good. Many nomads love it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Final Verdict -->
  <section id="verdict" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Malta's Nomad Residence Permit offers a unique combination: English-speaking EU country, Mediterranean climate, and established expat infrastructure. The €2,700/month threshold is accessible for most professional remote workers.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The main trade-offs are Malta's small size (you'll know every corner within months) and summer crowds. If you value compactness, safety, and English without language barriers, Malta delivers.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      For fintech/gaming professionals, Malta is particularly attractive given the industry concentration. For others, it's a comfortable, well-organized EU base with excellent weather and easy European travel.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-primary-800 mb-4">
        Malta's Nomad Residence Permit offers up to 3 years in an English-speaking EU island nation. Get proper health insurance (€40-150/month), prove €2,700/month income, secure accommodation, and enjoy Mediterranean living with full Schengen mobility.
      </p>
